  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "We qualify participants by first asking them a screening question at the beginning of the survey, and then verifying answers manually to disregard answers provided by those who fail the screening.",
    "We require participants to be physically located in the U.S. and to speak English as a first language.",
    "For each human participant study, we source a distinct set of participants (no overlap) to avoid potential bias in annotations that could occur from participating in related studies in the past.",
    "For each study, we measure the average inter-annotator agreement using Fleiss's kappa (Fleiss, 1971).",
    "We choose ChatGPT (OpenAI, 2022) (gpt-3.5-turbo-0613) as the LLM we use in the implementation."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "For each study, we measure the average inter-annotator agreement using Fleiss's kappa (Fleiss, 1971)."
  ]
}